== 反响 ==
=== 票房 ===
《木乃伊》于1999年5月7日上映，首周在美国3210家电影院收入4300万美元，最终本土票房达到1亿5538万5488美元，其他国家2亿6054万7918美元，全球总计4亿1593万3406美元<ref>{{cite web | title = ''The Mummy'' | publisher = [[Box_Office_Mojo|Box Office Mojo]]                        | archivedate = 2014-01-24 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140124155137/http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=mummy.htm | url = http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=mummy.htm | accessdate = 2014-02-11}}</ref>。

=== 专业评价 ===
《木乃伊》所获评价褒贬不一。根据[[烂蕃茄|烂蕃茄]]上收集的82篇评论文章来看，其中45篇给出了“新鲜”的正面评价，“新鲜度”为60%，平均得分5.7（最高十分）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1087270-mummy/ |title=The Mummy |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=2014-02-11 |archivedate=2014-01-04 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140104035058/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1087270-mummy/}}</ref>。而在[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]上收集的34篇评论中则有11篇给出好评，7篇差评，16篇褒贬不一，综合评分48（最高100）<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-mummy |title=The Mummy: Reviews |publisher=[[CBS公司|CBS]] |work=Metacritic |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024225350/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-mummy |accessdate=2014-02-11 |archivedate=2012-10-24}}</ref>。《[[芝加哥论坛报|芝加哥论坛报]]》影评人[[罗杰·艾伯特|罗杰·艾伯特]]给予本片三星（最高四星）的评价，他在评论中表示：“很难说我到底喜欢这部电影的哪个方面，但我几乎对其中的每时每刻都感到享受。无论是剧本、导演、表演甚至里面那个木-{乃}-伊都说不上有什么出彩之处，但我看得一点也不闷，有时还很没道理地感到愉快”<ref>{{cite news |last=Ebert |first=Roger |title=''The Mummy'' |publisher=Chicago Sun-Times |date=1999-05-07 |quote=There is hardly a thing I can say in its favor, except that I was cheered by nearly every minute of it. I cannot argue for the script, the direction, the acting or even the mummy, but I can say that I was not bored and sometimes I was unreasonably pleased. |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-mummy-1999 |accessdate=2014-02-11 |archivedate=2014-01-04 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140104105821/http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-mummy-1999 |deadurl=no}}</ref>。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》的欧文·格雷伯曼（{{lang|en|Owen Gleiberman}}）给予影片的评价为“{{lang|en|B-}}”（最高{{lang|en|A+}}），称“《木乃伊》想要让你感到不寒而悚，但在试图做到这一点的同时又放不开那些与这一目标不搭界的玩笑”<ref>{{cite news|last=Gleiberman |first=Owen |title=''The Mummy'' |publisher=Entertainment Weekly |date=1999-05-07 |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,64020,00.html |accessdate=2014-02-11 |quote=would like to make you shudder, but it tries to do so without ever letting go of its jocular inconsequentiality. |archivedate=2013-05-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130528144612/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0%2C%2C64020%2C00.html |deadurl=no }}</ref>。《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》的鲍勃·格雷厄姆（{{lang|en|Bob Graham}}）对本片的演员表演和特技效果给予了高度评价<ref>{{cite news |author=Graham, Bob |title='Mummy' -- It's Alive |publisher=San Francisco Chronicle |date=1999-05-07 |accessdate=2008-02-03}}</ref>。

《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的斯蒂芬·霍尔登（{{lang|en|Stephen Holden}}）写道：“这个版本的《木乃伊》没有自命不凡地去假装与一部搬上银幕的花里胡哨漫画视频游戏有任何不同之处。可以想象成配上动画人物的《[[法櫃奇兵|夺宝奇兵]]》，但没有其中连贯的故事情节，特技效果也很俗气。（或是）想象成将其中真正的恐怖剥离，再重新包装成埃及主题[[万圣夜|万圣节]]舞会的《[[活死人之夜|活死人之夜]]》，（还可以）想象为《[[两傻大战隐形人|两傻大战隐形人]]》（{{lang|en|''Abbott and Costello Meet the Mummy''}}）移植为一部[[平·克劳斯贝|平·克劳斯贝]]和[[鲍勃·霍普|鲍勃·霍普]]的[[公路片|公路片]]，并且配上史诗规模的风格恶搞。”<ref>{{cite news |last=Holden |first=Stephen |title=Sarcophagus, Be Gone: Night of the Living Undead |publisher=The New York Times |date=1999-05-07 |quote=This version of ''The Mummy'' has no pretenses to be anything other than a gaudy comic video game splashed onto the screen. Think ''Raiders of the Lost Ark'' with cartoon characters, no coherent story line and lavish but cheesy special effects. Think ''Night of the Living Dead'' stripped of genuine horror and restaged as an Egyptian-theme Halloween pageant. Think ''Abbott and Costello Meet the Mummy'' grafted onto a road picture and pumped up into an epic-size genre spoof. |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1999/05/07/movies/film-review-sarcophagus-be-gone-night-of-the-living-undead.html |accessdate=2014-02-12 |archivedate=2013-11-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131113010419/http://www.nytimes.com/1999/05/07/movies/film-review-sarcophagus-be-gone-night-of-the-living-undead.html}}</ref>《奥斯汀纪事报》（{{lang|en|''The Austin Chronicle''}}）和《达拉斯观察报》（{{lang|en|''Dallas Observer''}}）得出的结论认为，虽然表演和特技效果表现都不错，但这部电影缺乏凝聚力<ref name="observer" /><ref>{{cite news |author=Savlov, Mark |title=The Mummy |publisher=The Austin Chronicle |date=1999-05-07 |archivedate=2013-11-12 |deadurl=no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131112212008/http://www.austinchronicle.com/calendar/film/1999-05-07/the-mummy/ |url=http://www.austinchronicle.com/calendar/film/1999-05-07/the-mummy/ |accessdate=2014-02-12}}</ref>，《达拉斯观察报》感叹，影片虽然特技效果出色，但电影本身却没有灵魂，而这本该是一件很容易的事情<ref name="observer">{{cite news |author=Hinson, Hal |url=http://www.dallasobserver.com/1999-05-13/film/mummy-dearest/ |title=Mummy dearest |quote= If only generating a soul for the film itself were so easy. |publisher=Dallas Observer |date=1999-05-07 |archivedate=2013-11-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131112145847/http://www.dallasobserver.com/1999-05-13/film/mummy-dearest/ |deadurl=no |accessdate=2014-02-12}}</ref>。其它一些媒体出版物认为工业光魔公司制作的特技效果对本片产生了不利影响，如《跳接》（{{lang|en|''Jump Cut''}}）的欧内斯特·拉尔森（{{lang|en|Ernest Larson}}）就觉得《木乃伊》“是标准的工业光魔公司作品”<ref>{{cite journal |first=Ernest |last=Larsen |title=The Mummy: traffic in mummies |journal=Jump Cut |deadurl=no |url=http://ejumpcut.org/archive/onlinessays/JC43folder/Mummy.html |date=2000-07 | issue=43 |pages=12-15, 128 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131112150033/http://ejumpcut.org/archive/onlinessays/JC43folder/Mummy.html |archivedate=2013-11-12 |accessdate=2014-02-12}}</ref>。[[英国电影协会|英国电影协会]]的金·纽曼（{{lang|en|Kim Newman}}）认为本片与数十年前的原作相比有所不及，因为所有的时间都花在了特技效果上，没有营造出像原作那样经典的气氛<ref name="bfi" />。《[[今日美国|今日美国]]》给电影的评价为两星（最高四星），认为影片“未能免俗”<ref name="usa today" />，英国电影协会也有同样的看法<ref name="bfi">{{cite web |author=Newman, Kim |date=1999-06-01 |archivedate=2012-05-17 |url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/sightandsound/review/152 |title=Sight and Sound: The Mummy |work=British Film Institute |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120517170543/http://www.bfi.org.uk/sightandsound/review/152 |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2012-05-17}}</ref>。《今日美国》的评价中这样写道：“要是（片中）有人抱怨说有什么气味难闻，你就可以肯定镜头中将会出现一个阿拉伯人走卒。武器、拳头和俏皮话都一样快的费舍或许能让这一天不至太过难熬，但即便是他也无法让这成为一部好电影。”<ref name="usa today">{{cite news |last=Wloszczyna |first=Susan |title=Effects New Curse of ''The Mummy'' |publisher=USA Today |date=1999-05-07 |quote=If someone complains of a foul odor, you can be sure an Arab stooge is about to enter a scene. Fraser, equally quick with weapon, fist or quip, may save the day, but even he can't save the picture}}</ref>

